# Interactive controls: pointer cursor (global affordance)

Users should see the **pointer (hand) cursor** over the full clickable region, including when the pointer is over nested **text** or **SVG/icons**. Some browsers default nested nodes to `cursor: auto`, which reads as “not clickable.”

## Required behavior

1. **Root interactive element** (`<button>`, `<a href>`, large icon hit targets): set `cursor: pointer` (Tailwind `cursor-pointer` or plain CSS).
2. **Descendants** inside that control: `cursor: inherit` on children (or a single rule like `.my-cta * { cursor: inherit }`) so label + icon match the parent.
3. **Disabled** interactive elements: `cursor: not-allowed` (and keep inherited cursor off misleading “clickable” affordance).

## Optional global baseline (site CSS)

For marketing/landing sites without heavy custom button chrome, a small global layer in `globals.css` (or equivalent) keeps behavior consistent:

```css
a[href]:not([aria-disabled="true"]) {
  cursor: pointer;
}
a[href] * {
  cursor: inherit;
}
button:not(:disabled) {
  cursor: pointer;
}
button:not(:disabled) * {
  cursor: inherit;
}
button:disabled {
  cursor: not-allowed;
}
```

Narrow or override per component when a control intentionally uses another cursor (`wait`, `text`, resize handles, etc.).

## CTA motion: translate + transition gotcha

If a **hover nudge** (e.g. arrow sliding right) uses CSS `transition-property: transform` but Tailwind’s `translate-x-*` utilities map to the separate **`translate`** longhand (common in modern Tailwind), the **transition may not run**—motion looks instant or broken.

**Fix:** drive the nudge with **`transform: translate3d(...)`** in your own class (see `makeacompany-ai` `.waitlist-cta-arrow`), or add `translate` to `transition-property`. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

